        <p>Small contractors — 1 to 10 people — often get sold software that's too complex, too expensive, or designed for companies 10x their size. These recommendations are specifically for small contracting businesses that need real tools without enterprise overhead.</p>

        <h2>What small contractors actually need</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>Fast, professional estimates that win jobs</li>
          <li>Simple job tracking without a 6-hour onboarding course</li>
          <li>Invoicing and payment collection</li>
          <li>Basic scheduling and task management</li>
          <li>Photo and document storage per project</li>
          <li>Affordable pricing — under $150/month ideally</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Top picks for small contractors</h2>

        <h3>Houzz Pro — Best overall for small residential contractors</h3>
        <p>At $85/month, Houzz Pro is the best combination of value and capability for small residential contractors. You get estimates, invoicing, project management, client communication, and — uniquely — a public profile on Houzz that generates inbound leads from homeowners in your market.</p>

        <p>For a small remodeler or specialty contractor who's been running on spreadsheets, Houzz Pro is the upgrade that pays for itself. The lead generation alone is worth the cost in most markets.</p>

